### Pro-Tip for your Ubuntu Setup
Since you mentioned troubleshooting your Dell laptop's hardware, remember that `pynvme` **unbinds** the drive from the Linux Kernel. 
> **Warning:** While a script is running, your OS cannot see the drive (it won't show up in `lsblk`). Once you finish testing, you must run `make reset` to give the drive back to Ubuntu so you can access your files again.

